The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | EB to follow Subhas wish
                                                   EB to follow Subhas wish
            A STAFF REPORTER                                  
	Calcutta: East Bengal will go by Subhas Bhowmicks wishes when they recruit players for the next football season. The club hasnt won a trophy in the ongoing season.         
	We will strictly follow Subhas list of players while recruiting players for the next season, club president Pranab Dasgupta said Tuesday after announcing their decision to retain Bhowmick as coach.         
	Though it was finalised on Tuesday that Bhowmick would keep his job, East Bengals executive committee took about one-and-a-half hours to finalise the whole issue.         
	We have unanimously decided to go on with Subhas as our coach. There was no second name discussed and we are happy to retain him as our coach, Dasgupta said.         
	According to Dasgupta, Bhowmicks contract will be till the end of the season and there will be no hike in his salary. But the coach will earn incentive for each trophy he wins for the club. It was learnt that Bhowmick will present his list to the club East Bengal finish their I-League engagements.         
	The club has also decided to seek former players suggestions in recruiting players. The club will also form a football core-committee to oversee the team formation for the upcoming season.         
	Meanwhile, the club will lose about Rs 70 lakh after one of the co-sponsors withdrew their contract on Tuesday.                                                                                                                       
